								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">ut quÃ¦rerent misericordiam a facie Dei cÃ¦li super sacramento isto, et non perirent Daniel et socii ejus cum ceteris sapientibus Babylonis.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">To the end that they should ask mercy at the face of the God of heaven concerning this secret, and that Daniel and his companions might not perish with the rest of the wise men of Babylon.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">18</div> <div class="vers-content">and would have them cry out upon the God of heaven for better knowledge of his secret, without which both he and they should perish in the general massacre of the wise men.</div></div></td>
